OL,3,CFamily's criticism after father's
OL,4,Ckiller moved to open prison
OL,6,F"When I was told she would serve 14
OL,7,Fyears to then be told she would be
OL,8,Fmoved to an open prison getting day
OL,9,Frelease four years before. She
OL,10,Fshouldn't have that privilege."
OL,12,FMiss O'Brien said she was contacted
OL,13,Ftwo years into the sentence to be told
OL,14,FGlover would be allowed to attend her
OL,15,Fmother's funeral, which caused her
OL,16,Fdistress as the ceremony had been at
OL,17,Fthe same place her father was laid to
OL,18,Frest.
